Good morning, James,

04:01.486 --> 04:04.280
Mrs, Greenway, you're looking
mighty pretty today,

04:04.405 --> 04:06.199
Thank you, Billy,
hand this to the warden,

04:06.282 --> 04:08.159
You know how he loves
your letters,

04:08.201 --> 04:10.202
Don't be making
those prisoners write,

04:10.369 --> 04:12.454
Teddy is almost finished
with the new porch,

04:12.538 --> 04:14.331
I know it's extravagant,
but it's a way

04:14.456 --> 04:17.918
to give your brother money
without it seeming like a handout,

04:17.959 --> 04:20.086
You know how Jane is,

04:20.212 --> 04:23.006
You have any message
for him?

04:24.507 --> 04:25.633
What do you think?

04:27.802 --> 04:30.221
I'll give your love
to Melanie,

04:30.221 --> 04:32.640
She is head over heels
with this Bruce creature,

04:32.848 --> 04:36.059
I'm hoping it's just
a teenage thing,

04:36.059 --> 04:37.394
Rosie sends her love,

04:37.436 --> 04:41.189
She's just found your old
G, I, Joe watch in the attic,

04:41.189 --> 04:43.066
She's having it
repaired,

04:43.149 --> 04:45.693
So you let
that be a surprise,

05:00.665 --> 05:02.709
[Sniffling]

05:04.711 --> 05:07.588
The sign said
don't mess with Texas!

05:07.713 --> 05:10.383
Texas certainly has
messed with me,

05:10.466 --> 05:11.509
[Pop]

05:11.592 --> 05:12.843
Oh! What is it?

05:26.814 --> 05:29.108
Why do you do this
to yourself, Granny?

05:29.150 --> 05:30.067
Give up, huh?

05:30.151 --> 05:31.569
Tommy's never
gonna change,

05:31.569 --> 05:32.945
Teddy, you're never
gonna change,

05:32.987 --> 05:34.363
Tommy has to change,

05:34.530 --> 05:37.908
No human being can
carry that much hostility

05:37.908 --> 05:39.159
his entire life,

05:39.284 --> 05:41.536
Granny, it's his third
possessions charge,

05:41.661 --> 05:43.121
Face it, Tommy's
a screw-up.

05:43.163 --> 05:45.915
You're never gonna be
a screw-up, are you, Bump?

05:46.040 --> 05:48.042
Shut up, butthole!

05:48.084 --> 05:51.670
That's his new thing,
calling people butthole,

05:55.799 --> 05:58.885
For she's a jolly
good butthole

05:59.010 --> 06:01.012
For she's a jolly
good butthole

06:01.054 --> 06:04.641
For she's a jolly
good butthole

06:04.766 --> 06:06.893
'Cause nobody can deny

06:07.018 --> 06:11.981
I sense Jane's child-rearing
philosophy here,

06:11.981 --> 06:13.565
We've got
some good news,

06:13.607 --> 06:15.943
What is it, another
illegitimate child?

06:16.109 --> 06:17.319
Granny,

06:17.319 --> 06:19.070
Jane's found a job,

06:19.112 --> 06:21.448
At the Stop 'n Go,

06:21.489 --> 06:24.242
Now that she's finally
embarked on a career,

06:24.284 --> 06:27.120
perhaps the 2 of you
would consider marriage,

06:27.120 --> 06:28.955
Of course not,

06:29.038 --> 06:31.457
[Military Music Plays]

07:00.734 --> 07:02.110
Oh, God!

07:02.318 --> 07:03.570
Bruce alert!

07:14.038 --> 07:14.913
Oh!

07:14.997 --> 07:16.832
Oh, God!

07:16.999 --> 07:18.500
Granny!

07:18.583 --> 07:20.252
Shouldn't you be in
20th century literature?

07:20.418 --> 07:22.754
Virginia Woolf
makes my skin crawl,

07:22.796 --> 07:25.590
and Bruce wanted to go
for a ride,

07:25.590 --> 07:27.216
so, you know,

07:27.300 --> 07:28.968
I can see that,

07:29.051 --> 07:30.761
That's not
really my car,

07:30.803 --> 07:32.346
My friend Tony
just lets me drive it,

07:32.388 --> 07:35.057
I don't care who owns
the pimp mobile,

07:35.140 --> 07:36.934
I did not raise
my granddaughter

07:37.059 --> 07:38.101
to have sex with
the likes of you,

07:38.143 --> 07:40.270
Granny, get out
of my room!

07:45.358 --> 07:47.485
Oh, God!

07:47.485 --> 07:48.819
Bruce: Ha ha ha!

07:50.071 --> 07:52.448
Afternoon, General,

07:52.531 --> 07:54.033
What's going on?

07:54.241 --> 07:55.868
Life as we know it,

08:06.002 --> 08:07.795
[Classical Music
Plays]

08:07.920 --> 08:09.338
I love Bruce,

08:09.380 --> 08:10.965
I hate you!

08:16.136 --> 08:18.680
Why? Because I care
what happens to you?

08:18.680 --> 08:20.181
No, It's because

08:20.307 --> 08:22.767
you're suffocating me!

08:24.060 --> 08:25.311
[Car Radio
Plays]

08:25.520 --> 08:26.521
Well,,, ha,

08:26.521 --> 08:27.939
Your, uh...
Your buddy Tony

08:28.064 --> 08:29.315
has great taste
in cars,

08:29.440 --> 08:30.858
Bruce,
start the car!

08:30.900 --> 08:32.735
Hey, Mel,
you didn't tell me

08:32.860 --> 08:34.653
you were riding around
in Ferraris,

08:34.736 --> 08:35.654
Aah! Drive!

08:39.282 --> 08:40.659
See you, Mel!

08:40.659 --> 08:42.910
[Honks Horn]

08:44.203 --> 08:45.955
Look, Granny,

08:48.583 --> 08:50.960
I'll get you more,

09:02.554 --> 09:04.889
The troops need
a morale boost,

09:09.435 --> 09:11.187
You can love 'em,

09:11.270 --> 09:13.105
but you can't
live their lives,

09:13.188 --> 09:15.983
Neither can they,
Not properly,

09:16.066 --> 09:18.860
The pain the children
claim to be in,,,

09:18.944 --> 09:19.986
it's exhausting,

09:20.070 --> 09:24.032
I can't do it,
I've had it, I can't go on,

09:24.157 --> 09:25.366
Nonsense,
Of course you can,

09:25.366 --> 09:27.368
Life is just
an uphill battle,

09:27.368 --> 09:29.161
You gotta keep on
fighting,

09:29.245 --> 09:32.164
You must figure out why
you lose the battles you lose

09:32.206 --> 09:34.750
and pray like hell
you win the war,

09:36.293 --> 09:38.170
Rosie,
what time is it?

09:38.170 --> 09:39.546
3:30,

09:39.546 --> 09:42.340
I'm going to bed,

09:42.465 --> 09:44.217
This day is over,

09:49.847 --> 09:51.432
This is not good,

09:51.640 --> 09:53.642
This is not good,

10:00.232 --> 10:01.066
Hey,
Jimmie Lee,

10:01.191 --> 10:01.983
Hey, girl,

10:02.192 --> 10:03.067
She here?

10:03.193 --> 10:04.986
Yes, she's cleaning
out that closet,

10:05.069 --> 10:06.404
Just come on in,

10:08.239 --> 10:10.241
I'm worried
about her, Patsy,

10:10.366 --> 10:13.035
She went to bed
yesterday at 3:30,

10:13.160 --> 10:15.454
She hasn't
gotten up yet,

10:15.537 --> 10:18.290
She's probably headed
for the big snap,

10:18.415 --> 10:19.749
Long overdue,

10:19.833 --> 10:22.168
Give these to Mel,
would you?

10:22.252 --> 10:24.420
She's been crying
a lot,

10:26.089 --> 10:27.465
It's her guilt,

10:27.507 --> 10:28.716
Manifesting itself

10:28.841 --> 10:29.884
finally,

10:30.009 --> 10:32.720
You know she's gotta
be feeling responsibility

10:32.803 --> 10:35.597
for all the problems
those kids are having...

10:35.639 --> 10:37.516
problems they never
woulda had

10:37.599 --> 10:39.392
if I'da raised 'em,,,

10:39.518 --> 10:41.811
like Emma wanted,

10:42.020 --> 10:43.229
Well,,,

10:43.354 --> 10:44.188
you didn't,

10:44.314 --> 10:45.189
Aurora did,

10:45.231 --> 10:47.608
Now we're stuck with
the consequences,

10:47.733 --> 10:50.569
Not like you did such
a great job with your own kids,

10:50.569 --> 10:52.863
You don't even know
where they are

10:52.947 --> 10:54.281
half the time,

10:54.364 --> 10:56.283
I get the credit card
bills,

10:56.283 --> 10:59.536
I can track 'em down
if I have to,

10:59.661 --> 11:01.955
Oh, I just wanna
do something

11:02.080 --> 11:03.498
about Aurora's moods,

11:03.540 --> 11:05.917
When she's pissed off,
we all drown,

11:05.917 --> 11:07.168
- Cheers,
- Cheers,

11:11.130 --> 11:13.048
She needs
professional help,

11:14.466 --> 11:16.343
Always has,

11:16.468 --> 11:17.803
Therapy?

11:17.844 --> 11:19.679
Well, why not?

11:21.014 --> 11:22.348
12 years of therapy

11:22.390 --> 11:25.184
made me the woman
I am today,

11:25.310 --> 11:26.394
[Clicks Tongue]

11:26.519 --> 11:27.937
O, K,

11:27.937 --> 11:31.732
How are we gonna get Aurora
Greenway to see a shrink?

11:31.732 --> 11:34.151
Eew, you got me,

11:46.537 --> 11:48.414
"Depressed?

11:48.456 --> 11:49.915
Bummed?"

11:49.999 --> 11:51.458
Cute,

12:01.885 --> 12:02.969
[Sighs]
Ohh,,,

12:02.969 --> 12:05.346
I don't know,

12:05.346 --> 12:08.140
I feel
so depressed,,,

12:08.182 --> 12:10.684
bummed,

12:10.768 --> 12:13.520
I know I'm surrounded
by people who love me,

12:13.562 --> 12:16.440
but I just can't
seem to snap out of it,

12:16.565 --> 12:18.358
Even here
at the beach?

12:18.442 --> 12:20.110
You love it here,

12:20.193 --> 12:22.112
I know, I know,

12:22.195 --> 12:24.030
Well, what can I do
to help?

12:24.030 --> 12:26.866
I think I need to
see a therapist,

12:27.950 --> 12:30.453
Good! Good for you,

12:30.494 --> 12:31.871
Huh?

12:32.037 --> 12:33.414
I think that's good,

12:33.455 --> 12:34.748
You,,, confront
your demons,

12:34.832 --> 12:36.458
wrestle with 'em,

12:36.500 --> 12:38.418
I'm gonna make
an appointment,

12:38.418 --> 12:39.419
Excellent,

12:41.796 --> 12:43.590
Would you go
with me?

12:43.715 --> 12:45.049
Sure, Of course,

12:48.010 --> 12:49.345
Rosie, this can't be it,

12:49.470 --> 12:50.346
Yep,

12:50.388 --> 12:51.305
Where?

12:51.347 --> 12:52.264
3106,

12:52.348 --> 12:53.307
This house?

12:53.349 --> 12:55.142
Well, there's his sign, too,
That's it,

12:55.184 --> 12:57.060
Rosie, this does not
feel professional,

12:57.144 --> 12:58.937
Where did you
find this man?

12:59.062 --> 13:01.314
He came highly
recommended,

13:03.107 --> 13:05.902
I wish you would
come in with me,

13:05.985 --> 13:07.320
Please?

13:09.488 --> 13:11.448
I think I'd better,

13:11.490 --> 13:12.283
Oh, dear,

13:14.660 --> 13:17.245
Man singing:
There beyond the sea

13:17.371 --> 13:20.832
Somewhere waiting
for me

13:20.832 --> 13:24.836
[Singing]

13:28.297 --> 13:29.632
Somewhere,,,

13:29.757 --> 13:32.760
I'll be waiting for you
in the car, Rosie,

13:32.843 --> 13:34.136
You have to stay!

13:34.219 --> 13:35.387
I don't have
to stay,

13:35.512 --> 13:36.346
Oh!

13:36.430 --> 13:37.889
You don't need me

13:37.889 --> 13:40.308
to spew out the grim little
details of your childhood,

13:40.350 --> 13:42.435
The appointment's not for me,
It's for you,

13:42.519 --> 13:43.686
I lied,

13:43.811 --> 13:45.646
EXcuse me?

13:45.688 --> 13:48.357
You're the one who's been
so depressed lately,

13:48.441 --> 13:49.817
Rosie, I don't need
therapy,

13:49.859 --> 13:51.068
Why, the very idea!

13:51.152 --> 13:55.030
Now I suggest that
you go back in there

13:55.155 --> 13:56.657
and you keep
your appointment,

13:56.740 --> 13:57.866
Aurora!

13:58.992 --> 13:59.868
[Singing]

13:59.868 --> 14:00.785
[Ding Dong]

14:00.910 --> 14:02.412
Be right there!

14:05.832 --> 14:06.791
Mrs, Greenway?

14:10.503 --> 14:11.545
Yes,

14:11.587 --> 14:12.880
Jerry Bruckner,

14:12.963 --> 14:14.798
God, I am running
so late today,

14:14.882 --> 14:16.633
I'm sorry,
Please come on in,

14:16.758 --> 14:18.009
- Oh, sorry,
- No, I apologize,

14:18.093 --> 14:19.511
Forgive me,

14:19.594 --> 14:22.388
We have been
the victims of, uh,,,

14:22.514 --> 14:23.765
a very elaborate
ruse.

14:23.848 --> 14:24.807
Oh,

14:24.891 --> 14:27.518
Yes, my maid tricked me
into coming here,

14:27.518 --> 14:28.686
Oh,

14:28.811 --> 14:31.981
I,,, Dr, Bruckner,
I wasn't seeking analysis,

14:32.064 --> 14:33.440
and I'm not now,

14:33.482 --> 14:35.984
I'm not a doctor,
I'm a licensed counselor,

14:36.068 --> 14:37.986
What does that mean,
Mr, Bruckner?

14:38.070 --> 14:40.780
I listen, I try
to make people feel better,

14:40.864 --> 14:42.991
Well,,,

14:43.116 --> 14:44.951
sorry for
the misunderstanding,

14:44.993 --> 14:48.371
Obviously my maid
is the one who is disturbed,

14:48.537 --> 14:51.749
I'm surrounded by the most
taxing array of lunatics,

14:54.168 --> 14:55.502
Me, too,

14:55.544 --> 14:56.545
It's the job,

14:58.505 --> 14:59.881
Well, good-bye,

14:59.965 --> 15:02.217
And I'm clearly not
the sort of woman

15:02.300 --> 15:03.301
who would,,,

15:03.510 --> 15:06.304
be free in sharing
and revealing her secrets,

15:06.345 --> 15:07.555
You understand?

15:07.638 --> 15:09.307
Well, many people

15:09.432 --> 15:11.267
feel that way,

15:11.308 --> 15:13.394
It was a pleasure
meeting you,

15:13.435 --> 15:15.437
Do you have a card?

15:17.064 --> 15:18.607
Certainly,

15:23.820 --> 15:24.988
Thank you,

15:25.029 --> 15:26.406
Good-bye,
Mrs, Greenway,

15:26.489 --> 15:27.990
And I'm awfully
sorry.

15:28.157 --> 15:30.159
[Laughs]
Forget it,

15:31.535 --> 15:33.370
We'll meet, we'll meet,
we'll meet

15:33.454 --> 15:34.913
Beyond the shore

15:34.955 --> 15:36.248
We'll kiss,,,

15:36.331 --> 15:38.250
You are
so fucking fired,

15:38.333 --> 15:40.543
Yeah,,, right,

15:41.711 --> 15:43.338
Class, the quality
of your exams

15:43.505 --> 15:45.048
surprised even me,

15:45.089 --> 15:47.884
Some of you are even
beginning to grasp

15:48.009 --> 15:49.343
early 20th
century literature,

15:49.468 --> 15:50.302
[Bell Rings]

15:50.386 --> 15:51.887
That's it,
Class dismissed,

15:57.100 --> 15:58.810
Professor?

15:58.810 --> 15:59.769
Professor!

15:59.769 --> 16:01.646
A D-plus?
That sucks!

16:01.646 --> 16:04.565
Ms, Horton, your defense
of Rupert Brooke's Georgianism

16:04.565 --> 16:05.983
is flawed,

16:05.983 --> 16:08.736
What is the matter with bucking
conventional criticism?

16:08.861 --> 16:11.739
Brooke protested against
Victorianism and he kicked ass,

16:11.780 --> 16:13.157
and I deserve an "A,"

16:13.157 --> 16:15.159
No, Ms, Horton,
You don't,

16:17.536 --> 16:19.121
Yes, I do,

16:21.539 --> 16:23.708
Mmm!

16:23.917 --> 16:26.711
You are on the thinnest
of ice, Rosie,

16:28.087 --> 16:31.382
Perfect timing,
Duck Madagascar,

16:31.382 --> 16:33.300
Mmm, I've eaten,

16:37.387 --> 16:38.638
[Running Garbage
Disposal]

16:38.805 --> 16:40.640
I got hungry,
and so I ate,

16:40.640 --> 16:41.683
Jesus!

16:41.808 --> 16:43.143
Did I say anything?

16:43.184 --> 16:45.019
Oh, no,
Of course not,

16:45.019 --> 16:48.481
I should just be grateful
you went to class for a change,

16:48.564 --> 16:50.399
I'm gonna quit,

16:53.694 --> 16:56.780
Do you know how much Rice University
costs, Melanie?

16:56.780 --> 16:58.698
I had to sell
my Renoir

16:58.698 --> 17:00.533
so you could have
an education,

17:00.700 --> 17:03.703
Oh, I thought you sold the Renoir
for Teddy's braces,

17:03.745 --> 17:05.704
Or then again,
didn't you sell the Renoir

17:05.829 --> 17:07.832
for Tommy's legal
defense?

17:07.832 --> 17:09.250
The money from
that Renoir's

17:09.333 --> 17:12.670
like splinters from the true cross,
Everybody's got a piece!

17:12.670 --> 17:14.046
You are so ungrateful,

17:14.128 --> 17:16.839
You are the only one
of your mother's children

17:17.049 --> 17:19.259
that has a real chance
at a life,

17:19.384 --> 17:22.220
Why do you insist on being
so self-destructive?

17:22.220 --> 17:24.430
I'm not being
self-destructive!

17:24.555 --> 17:25.807
I'm just...

17:26.015 --> 17:27.808
Get off my back!

17:29.518 --> 17:31.353
Boy, if your mother
had lived,

17:31.395 --> 17:34.440
she would be so horrified
at the way you turned out,

17:34.565 --> 17:36.358
If my mother had lived,

17:36.441 --> 17:38.985
I wouldn't have
turned out this way,

17:39.110 --> 17:41.905
so horrible and such
a disappointment to you!

17:44.866 --> 17:46.284
Ooh!

17:50.121 --> 17:52.998
[Classical Music Plays]

17:54.458 --> 17:57.169
Tony, I'm telling you,
Stallone only eats egg whites,

17:57.252 --> 17:58.587
It's pure protein,

17:58.670 --> 18:00.005
[Knock On Door]

18:00.213 --> 18:01.589
Hang on a second,

18:04.384 --> 18:06.260
Melanie, what's up?

18:06.344 --> 18:08.221
I did it,
I moved out,

18:08.221 --> 18:10.139
I'm free,

18:10.139 --> 18:11.557
Lemme call you
back,

18:11.599 --> 18:13.559
Help me with my stuff!

18:13.559 --> 18:14.893
Huh?

18:16.520 --> 18:19.314
I feel like celebrating
and hitting the town!

18:19.314 --> 18:20.690
Where's that Ferrari?

18:20.690 --> 18:22.108
Uh, Tony needed it,

18:22.150 --> 18:23.484
This is so perfect!

18:23.693 --> 18:26.654
I shoulda done this
a long time ago,

18:26.696 --> 18:29.615
You and me,
starting our lives together,

18:29.657 --> 18:31.742
Doesn't it just
feel right?

18:31.867 --> 18:33.660
Uh, yeah,

18:33.660 --> 18:36.038
So how long
are you gonna stay?

18:36.038 --> 18:37.039
Forever!

18:37.080 --> 18:38.457
Oh, God,

18:40.000 --> 18:41.334
Mel is my hope,

18:41.418 --> 18:43.253
She is the smartest
and the cleverest

18:43.336 --> 18:44.587
of all my grandchildren,

18:44.796 --> 18:46.130
Ever since
their mother died,

18:46.214 --> 18:49.008
I have done nothing
but be there to help them

18:49.091 --> 18:50.468
and to love them

18:50.551 --> 18:53.345
and to try to instill values
that I thought were important, and...

18:53.345 --> 18:54.930
Don't you have
a real cup?

18:55.013 --> 18:57.140
I'm sorry, I don't,

18:57.140 --> 18:59.100
And now I'm
losing her,

18:59.142 --> 19:00.518
I see,

19:00.602 --> 19:02.437
What about
the children's father?

19:02.520 --> 19:04.856
Oh, Flap, no,
My goodness, no,

19:04.897 --> 19:06.732
Flap is not
father material,

19:06.858 --> 19:07.692
Flap,

19:07.817 --> 19:09.652
He wasn't husband
material, either,

19:09.694 --> 19:11.570
Flap is not
human material,

19:13.530 --> 19:15.407
He didn't
abandon them, really,

19:15.449 --> 19:17.284
Flap is just
very weak,

19:17.409 --> 19:19.161
He lives
in Santa Fe,

19:20.662 --> 19:23.540
So there's been no,,,
father figure at all?

19:26.000 --> 19:28.794
Well, actually,
there have been a few,

19:28.919 --> 19:32.631
I was involved several years ago
with a former general,

19:32.756 --> 19:35.134
His name is
Hector Scott,

19:35.217 --> 19:38.136
He was a father figure
to Melanie,

19:38.261 --> 19:40.305
And... And we broke up,

19:40.513 --> 19:42.265
Years ago,

19:42.307 --> 19:45.893
But he still continues
to terrorize me on a daily basis,

19:46.018 --> 19:46.894
Mmm,

19:46.936 --> 19:47.854
[Sniffs]

19:47.895 --> 19:49.897
[Sighs]

19:52.399 --> 19:55.444
And then many, many,,,

19:55.444 --> 19:57.988
many years ago,
I, um...

20:00.031 --> 20:02.951
My next door neighbor
was Garrett Breedlove,

20:06.788 --> 20:08.456
The astronaut,
The astronaut,

20:10.583 --> 20:12.459
[Laughs]
Oh, God,

20:12.543 --> 20:17.339
Well,,, Garrett Breedlove
possessed every single quality

20:17.381 --> 20:20.216
that I find repellent
in men,

20:20.300 --> 20:22.510
But it worked,

20:22.719 --> 20:24.887
For a while, it worked,

20:25.096 --> 20:26.889
Oh, the boys adored him,

20:26.889 --> 20:28.849
Melanie, well,,,

20:28.891 --> 20:30.643
she was too young,

20:30.768 --> 20:32.519
And then he moved away

20:32.645 --> 20:34.229
to, uh, Minneapolis,

20:34.438 --> 20:36.481
Milwaukee, or,,,

20:36.607 --> 20:37.816
whatever,

20:40.819 --> 20:43.530
This was a man
who orbited the Earth,

20:45.198 --> 20:46.991
And now he's married
with a family,

20:47.033 --> 20:48.784
Well, I just can't
picture that,

20:48.951 --> 20:51.453
Garrett was never very comfortable
around children,

20:51.537 --> 20:53.747
He only liked
dating them,

20:55.207 --> 20:58.168
Who was the great
love of your life?

21:03.339 --> 21:05.717
Oh,,,

21:05.758 --> 21:07.718
I haven't met him yet,

21:07.760 --> 21:08.844
Mmm,

21:10.554 --> 21:11.889
Well, Mrs, Greenway,

21:12.014 --> 21:13.849
your situation
is hardly unique,

21:14.016 --> 21:16.268
You've obviously
spent your whole life

21:16.310 --> 21:17.769
thinking
only of others,

21:19.187 --> 21:20.563
It's so true,

21:21.606 --> 21:23.733
You've neglected
yourself,

21:23.816 --> 21:24.817
I know,

21:26.569 --> 21:27.945
You are so bright,

21:28.070 --> 21:30.364
Just call 'em
like I see 'em,

21:32.533 --> 21:34.535
Well, I have
neglected my life,

21:34.618 --> 21:35.911
That's obvious,

21:35.953 --> 21:38.330
Well,,, it's been
so fast,

21:38.330 --> 21:40.290
It's all so fast,

21:40.332 --> 21:41.666
and it's so blurred,

21:41.708 --> 21:43.501
What is my life?

21:43.501 --> 21:45.420
What have I done?

21:45.420 --> 21:46.587
Oh,

21:46.712 --> 21:48.464
And what's it
all about?

21:51.717 --> 21:53.719
I think it's time
that I get strong,

21:53.719 --> 21:55.262
Yes,

21:55.304 --> 21:58.014
And that I ask myself
the really hard questions,

21:58.181 --> 21:59.599
Yes!

21:59.683 --> 22:02.018
It's time for you
to start taking care of you,

22:02.018 --> 22:04.771
Yes, I need to be,,,

22:04.771 --> 22:06.189
selfish,

22:06.230 --> 22:07.565
Yes,

22:07.565 --> 22:09.358
Selfish in the good sense,

22:09.567 --> 22:10.359
Absolutely,

22:10.401 --> 22:11.318
Yes?

22:11.360 --> 22:12.486
Absolutely,

22:19.618 --> 22:20.952
I see,

22:24.914 --> 22:25.832
Thank you,

22:27.500 --> 22:28.459
[Sighs]

22:28.459 --> 22:30.419
You've been
such a help,

22:32.796 --> 22:34.631
Oh, you don't
have to pay me now,

22:34.715 --> 22:36.466
It's easier
for patients to pay

22:36.550 --> 22:38.385
at the end of
each month by check,

22:38.468 --> 22:41.346
Well, I think you misunderstand
the... the visit,

22:41.388 --> 22:44.015
I only wanted
a period of quiet time

22:44.057 --> 22:46.392
so that I could
organize my thoughts,

22:46.434 --> 22:49.937
I can't imagine my requiring
your services on a regular basis,

22:49.937 --> 22:51.355
I won't be returning,

22:51.397 --> 22:53.232
Whatever you say,
Mrs, Greenway,

22:53.357 --> 22:55.108
Aurora,

23:03.241 --> 23:04.617
Ah,,, hi!

23:04.701 --> 23:06.494
A wave
and a smile,

23:06.619 --> 23:08.454
She must be
in a better mood,

23:08.496 --> 23:10.831
Lemme get out
the hats and horns,

23:10.915 --> 23:12.750
Rosie, I am starving!

23:12.833 --> 23:15.169
Arthur,

23:15.252 --> 23:16.253
Hi, Aurora,

23:19.548 --> 23:20.882
You got a call

23:21.007 --> 23:23.301
from someone named,
uh,,, Pasqual

23:23.384 --> 23:26.762
[French Accent]
Who wants you for dessert,

23:26.762 --> 23:28.139
Pascal,

23:28.139 --> 23:31.559
And he wants to have me over
for dessert,

23:31.559 --> 23:34.353
His English is less
than perfect, Hector,

23:34.394 --> 23:36.480
Are you having
an affair?

23:37.689 --> 23:38.482
W...

23:38.565 --> 23:39.983
Why, Hector,

23:40.108 --> 23:41.901
you're in no position

23:42.110 --> 23:44.946
to be inquisitive
or jealous,

23:49.116 --> 23:50.451
Now you go home

23:50.534 --> 23:53.037
and you rethink
your clothing,

23:56.707 --> 23:59.000
God, she's so full
of herself,

23:59.084 --> 24:01.211
At least it's
her old self,

24:01.252 --> 24:02.962
thank God,

24:44.917 --> 24:46.419
Oh, dear!

24:46.586 --> 24:49.588
Ha ha ha!

24:49.588 --> 24:51.549
What's all this?

24:53.550 --> 24:54.802
Every clipping,

24:54.885 --> 24:57.304
every diary, every letter,
every photograph,

24:57.346 --> 24:59.181
every theater program,

24:59.306 --> 25:01.099
Rosie,
this represents

25:01.182 --> 25:03.059
everything that's ever
happened to me,

25:03.101 --> 25:06.896
so I am going to
organize it

25:07.063 --> 25:09.065
and make sense
out of it all,

25:09.065 --> 25:12.067
Rosie, I'm gonna chronicle
every day of my life,

25:13.652 --> 25:15.237
What a mess,

25:15.237 --> 25:17.239
Oh,,, my,,,

25:17.239 --> 25:18.406
goodness!

25:18.448 --> 25:20.700
These,,, people
are all dead,

25:29.250 --> 25:30.334
[Music Plays]

25:30.459 --> 25:31.418
[Laughing]

25:31.418 --> 25:33.337
Man: Cut it out,

25:33.420 --> 25:34.713
Woman: I know,

25:34.713 --> 25:37.090
Wait, Ow, ow, ow,
You're on my head,

25:37.132 --> 25:37.966
[Laughter]

25:38.091 --> 25:39.259
Woman: Oh!

25:39.301 --> 25:40.218
Oh, God,

25:41.720 --> 25:44.180
Mel,,, this is not
what it seems,

25:44.180 --> 25:46.182
Get your clothes on,
Toni,

25:46.182 --> 25:47.850
Toni? That's Toni?

25:48.059 --> 25:50.102
Mel, we gotta talk,

25:50.102 --> 25:51.061
That's Mel?

25:51.061 --> 25:52.354
Mel!

25:52.438 --> 25:54.231
I got a better idea,

25:54.356 --> 25:55.232
Mel,

25:55.315 --> 25:56.191
Mel!

25:59.194 --> 26:00.237
Mel!

26:00.362 --> 26:02.113
Don't overreact,

26:09.745 --> 26:10.788
Great,

26:14.083 --> 26:15.709
[Grinding Gears]

26:19.880 --> 26:22.132
Nice car, Toni,

26:40.065 --> 26:41.399
[Ding Dong
Ding Ding]

26:41.483 --> 26:44.068
[Ding Ding Ding
Dong Dong]

26:44.152 --> 26:45.611
[Ding Ding Ding]

26:45.737 --> 26:47.780
Patsy!

26:49.532 --> 26:50.866
No,

26:54.369 --> 26:57.164
[Alarm Sounds]

27:09.258 --> 27:11.844
I can't believe you,

27:21.686 --> 27:24.188
[Telephone Rings]

27:27.316 --> 27:29.151
Hello. Please leave
a message

27:29.193 --> 27:30.736
when you hear
the D-sharp.

27:30.820 --> 27:31.946
[Beep]

27:31.987 --> 27:33.530
Woman: Aurora,
pick up the phone,

27:33.697 --> 27:35.282
Something's happened
to Melly,

27:35.532 --> 27:36.158
Patsy!

27:36.366 --> 27:37.367
Oh!

27:37.492 --> 27:39.369
Where is she?

27:39.369 --> 27:41.287
Poor girl!

27:41.329 --> 27:42.956
We've pumped
her stomach,

27:43.039 --> 27:45.833
It's almost impossible
to take a lethal overdose

27:45.917 --> 27:47.460
in this family of drug,

27:47.501 --> 27:48.836
It's a muscle relaxant,

27:49.045 --> 27:50.629
so she's just,,,
very relaxed,

27:50.629 --> 27:52.840
Unresponsive,

27:52.840 --> 27:54.299
[Beep Beep Beep Beep]

27:54.383 --> 27:55.259
Gel,

27:55.259 --> 27:56.718
Clear!

27:56.802 --> 27:57.636
EXcuse me!

27:57.761 --> 27:59.638
Oh, Melly!

27:59.804 --> 28:00.680
EXcuse me,

28:00.805 --> 28:01.890
[Gasps]
Melanie,

28:02.015 --> 28:02.849
Oh, Melanie!

28:02.932 --> 28:04.183
Poor Melly,

28:04.392 --> 28:05.768
Oh, my darling,

28:05.810 --> 28:07.019
What do they say?

28:07.145 --> 28:08.980
This is such
a cry for help,

28:09.146 --> 28:10.564
I'm here to answer it,

28:10.606 --> 28:13.400
Patsy, we don't need you anymore,
You can go,

28:13.484 --> 28:15.819
Thank you for your help,
Mel, wake up, honey,

28:15.903 --> 28:17.696
Well, honey,
it was my house she came to,

28:17.779 --> 28:19.156
Well, she probably
assumed

28:19.239 --> 28:21.116
that with your 40th
birthday coming up,

28:21.157 --> 28:22.992
there'd be plenty
of pills on hand,

28:23.117 --> 28:24.702
Good one, Granny,

28:24.702 --> 28:25.661
Oh!

28:25.661 --> 28:26.621
[Relieved
Giggles]

28:26.621 --> 28:27.538
Mel!

28:27.663 --> 28:30.207
Oh, God, Mel,
I am so sorry,

28:30.249 --> 28:31.167
Where's Toni?

28:31.250 --> 28:32.584
It's all my fault,

28:32.668 --> 28:34.503
There are too many people in here,
and we have rules,

28:34.586 --> 28:35.462
Melanie,

28:35.546 --> 28:36.880
Wait, Why
are you sorry?

28:37.005 --> 28:37.839
Come on, Sis,

28:37.964 --> 28:39.799
Oh, God, Oh, Mel,
please forgive me,

28:39.841 --> 28:40.884
Security!

28:41.009 --> 28:42.760
You didn't try
to kill yourself over Bruce?

28:42.802 --> 28:44.220
[Sobs]
Oh!

28:44.220 --> 28:46.931
One! Just one!
Everybody else out!

28:47.139 --> 28:48.933
All right,
We'll go quietly,

28:48.933 --> 28:50.351
You... You get out,

28:50.392 --> 28:51.310
Hi, Rosie,

28:51.352 --> 28:52.770
You get out... now!

28:52.895 --> 28:54.146
I'll be back,

28:54.229 --> 28:56.565
You take good care
of my baby,

28:56.732 --> 28:57.482
Bye, Rosie,

28:57.691 --> 28:58.483
[Rosie Sobs]

28:58.567 --> 29:02.487
That will be all,
thank you,

29:02.570 --> 29:05.281
Yeah, If you don't
let them both stay,

29:05.448 --> 29:08.659
you're gonna have some
more patients on your hands,

29:08.659 --> 29:09.618
Melanie,

29:09.660 --> 29:11.495
Please just let me
help you,

29:11.620 --> 29:13.455
Mel, I want you
to come home,

29:13.497 --> 29:15.582
and I'm gonna
cook you dinner,

29:15.666 --> 29:17.667
Why does Patsy's
friendship with Melanie

29:17.793 --> 29:19.794
bother you so much?

29:19.920 --> 29:22.547
Melly was 3 when
my daughter Emma died,

29:22.589 --> 29:24.382
Patsy was Emma's
best friend

29:24.382 --> 29:25.800
and worst influence,

29:25.883 --> 29:29.637
After Emma was gone, Patsy felt
that she should raise Melly,

29:29.762 --> 29:31.138
and I would not
have it,

29:31.263 --> 29:34.058
She thinks that she
could have done a better job

29:34.141 --> 29:35.517
than I did,

29:35.559 --> 29:37.811
But I did the best
that I could,

29:37.894 --> 29:39.688
I wanted her
to appreciate life,

29:39.813 --> 29:42.690
I wanted her to be
responsible,

29:42.732 --> 29:45.485
I wanted her to understand
the essential things,

29:45.568 --> 29:46.903
[Sighs]

29:46.986 --> 29:48.863
You want a lot,

29:48.863 --> 29:50.906
Is that so bad?

29:54.201 --> 29:56.453
Say, how's your chronicle
coming along?

29:59.956 --> 30:01.416
My chronicle,

30:01.416 --> 30:02.750
Ha ha ha,

30:02.792 --> 30:06.212
You know,
it's like, um,,,

30:06.212 --> 30:08.506
it's like composing
a symphony,

30:08.547 --> 30:13.302
I tried to write a symphony
when I was about 18,

30:13.344 --> 30:15.220
I love music,

30:15.304 --> 30:18.515
But I... I... I, um,
I never finished it,

30:18.557 --> 30:20.934
Well, you should,

30:21.059 --> 30:24.812
It's important to leave
something behind, isn't it?

30:24.896 --> 30:26.481
I think it is,

30:29.650 --> 30:31.360
Who is this?

30:34.279 --> 30:35.864
Her name's Lola,

30:35.864 --> 30:36.990
Lola,

30:38.867 --> 30:40.160
She's a showgirl?

30:40.201 --> 30:41.661
Vegas,

30:41.786 --> 30:43.746
Really?

30:43.788 --> 30:44.706
Mmm,

30:44.789 --> 30:45.665
Ha,

30:45.748 --> 30:47.959
She's my mother!

30:50.753 --> 30:51.962
She is!

30:52.046 --> 30:53.881
What?

30:53.964 --> 30:56.758
She's got the best legs
on the line,

30:56.842 --> 30:59.302
Oh, she's awesome,

30:59.386 --> 31:01.679
[Laughs]
Oh!

31:01.805 --> 31:03.681
This... This is,,,

31:03.681 --> 31:05.391
certainly interesting,

31:05.516 --> 31:07.435
Oh,,,

31:07.560 --> 31:09.437
you have no idea,

31:09.437 --> 31:11.855
Lola's had
a really rough life,

31:11.855 --> 31:13.232
but she... Boy,

31:13.315 --> 31:15.234
She always comes up
kickin',

31:15.234 --> 31:17.235
She's the reason
I became a therapist,

31:17.319 --> 31:20.196
I saw how much good
it did her,

31:20.196 --> 31:21.781
Oh, God,

31:21.948 --> 31:24.742
She's the best mom
in the whole world,

31:27.203 --> 31:28.412
Hmm,

31:28.537 --> 31:31.207
Now you make sure
that you tell her that,

31:32.499 --> 31:33.751
I guarantee you

31:33.834 --> 31:35.961
she needs to hear that
on occasion,

31:37.295 --> 31:39.339
Well,,, see you
next week,

31:39.506 --> 31:40.632
O, K,

31:44.260 --> 31:45.845
You've been
fighting again,

31:45.887 --> 31:47.763
Is it broken?

31:47.847 --> 31:49.181
Is it?

31:50.850 --> 31:53.185
All you've done
all your life is fight,

31:53.185 --> 31:55.187
Like you haven't?

31:55.270 --> 31:56.688
Warden Littlefield
tells me

31:56.813 --> 31:59.649
you're doing very well
with your computer training,

31:59.733 --> 32:02.569
What, are you
driving him crazy, too?

32:04.153 --> 32:07.532
Would you like it for me
just not to come here anymore?

32:07.532 --> 32:09.784
Teddy and Melanie
have given up on you,

32:09.909 --> 32:11.368
I don't care,

32:11.410 --> 32:14.288
Then why do you come here
and speak to me?

32:14.329 --> 32:16.331
Why do you
show up at all?

32:16.331 --> 32:19.084
'Cause if I don't,
it makes me seem uncooperative,

32:19.167 --> 32:21.086
Bad for my parole,

32:32.221 --> 32:34.598
[Radio Plays]

32:38.643 --> 32:40.520
Take your time,

32:45.400 --> 32:46.818
Go away,

32:48.235 --> 32:49.612
Mel,,,

32:49.695 --> 32:52.114
I, uh,,,

32:52.114 --> 32:54.491
I wanted to...
to think about us

32:54.533 --> 32:56.368
starting over again,
you know?

32:56.410 --> 32:58.703
I'm supposed to
take you back now

32:58.787 --> 33:00.664
because you got
your hair cut, Bruce?

33:00.705 --> 33:03.082
I've got an idea
about you and me,

33:03.291 --> 33:04.667
Can... Can we talk?

33:04.667 --> 33:06.502
No, I don't
think so,

33:06.669 --> 33:07.920
Come on, Mel,

33:09.839 --> 33:11.340
Let's take a drive,

33:11.465 --> 33:13.634
I'm in a pinto,

33:14.635 --> 33:16.011
It's the real me,

33:18.180 --> 33:20.432
Tch!
Don't touch me!

33:20.598 --> 33:22.016
Ahh,,,

33:28.564 --> 33:30.357
You wanna hear
my plan?

33:30.441 --> 33:31.817
Yeah,

33:31.901 --> 33:32.860
Show me, show me,
show me

33:32.943 --> 33:35.487
How you do that trick

33:35.571 --> 33:38.365
The one that
makes me scream

33:38.448 --> 33:40.450
One of those is...

33:40.492 --> 33:42.202
What are you doing?

33:42.285 --> 33:43.286
Wait,

33:56.214 --> 33:59.843
What do those guys
have that I don't?

33:59.968 --> 34:02.387
Absolutely nothing,

34:02.387 --> 34:04.389
That's right,

34:04.514 --> 34:06.015
I'm gonna be a model,

34:06.182 --> 34:07.767
I'm serious,

34:07.934 --> 34:09.143
And then,

34:09.143 --> 34:11.562
after I've made
enough money modeling,

34:11.562 --> 34:12.938
I'll start acting,

34:13.063 --> 34:14.731
That's how it's done,
Mel,

34:14.731 --> 34:16.483
Whoo,

34:16.565 --> 34:19.360
I thought I was the one
that took the drugs,

34:23.114 --> 34:24.407
Mel,,,

34:24.489 --> 34:26.117
I almost blew it
with us,

34:26.242 --> 34:28.286
I don't want that
to happen again,

34:28.411 --> 34:30.286
I wanna take you
somewhere,,,

34:30.286 --> 34:31.914
where I can make
a life for us,

34:31.996 --> 34:34.416
There's too much
in the way here,

34:34.416 --> 34:38.210
I wanna go where
there'll be no distractions,

34:38.295 --> 34:39.420
Los Angeles?

34:39.420 --> 34:40.839
Bruce really loves me,

34:40.839 --> 34:43.757
And he wants to go somewhere
and start over fresh

34:43.800 --> 34:45.635
in a place where
we can be happy,

34:45.760 --> 34:48.554
There are 6 million
happy people here in Houston,

34:48.596 --> 34:51.389
I have no possibility
of being happy here,

34:51.389 --> 34:52.850
Why?

34:52.933 --> 34:55.268
You spray this house
with happiness repellent!

34:55.351 --> 34:56.186
Thank you,

34:56.311 --> 34:58.105
I will be happy
with Bruce,

34:58.188 --> 34:59.940
and Bruce is gonna
be happy in L, A,

35:00.106 --> 35:01.941
I was stationed in L, A,
after the war,

35:02.067 --> 35:04.193
I never had so much sex
in my life,

35:04.319 --> 35:06.112
This is for Tommy,

35:06.195 --> 35:08.114
This is for Teddy,
This is for the loathsome Jane...

35:08.197 --> 35:10.116
Granny, will you
listen to me?!

35:10.116 --> 35:13.452
You keep telling me
you want me to have a future,

35:13.452 --> 35:14.620
Yes,

35:14.661 --> 35:16.330
Well, I can't have
a future here,

35:16.455 --> 35:18.081
What are you gonna
do for money?

35:18.206 --> 35:19.457
Bruce has a plan,

35:19.541 --> 35:20.667
And what is that?

35:20.792 --> 35:24.003
It's a good plan,
and, um,,,

35:24.003 --> 35:25.963
if that doesn't
work out,

35:25.963 --> 35:28.132
I always have things
I can sell,

35:28.257 --> 35:29.592
Your mother's jewelry,

35:29.592 --> 35:30.759
At last,

35:30.759 --> 35:33.554
I have been so anxious
to get rid of it,

35:34.930 --> 35:36.682
Well,,,

35:36.807 --> 35:40.393
there's always Patsy,
Yeah, she can help me,

35:40.518 --> 35:42.312
Oh, another extremely
good idea,

35:42.395 --> 35:43.730
Call Patsy, Absolutely,

35:43.855 --> 35:46.149
Darling, sweet, kind,
generous, happy Patsy,

35:46.232 --> 35:47.441
Perfect Patsy

35:47.483 --> 35:49.068
from whom
all blessings flow,

35:49.110 --> 35:51.862
Let up on Patsy!
She doesn't hate you,

35:51.862 --> 35:54.781
I don't know why
you hate her so much,

35:54.781 --> 35:57.784
I don't hate Patsy, No, not at all,
Patsy is family,

35:57.909 --> 36:00.870
I love Patsy!
This is for Patsy,

36:04.832 --> 36:06.584
What are you doing?

36:06.709 --> 36:08.586
Generosity,

36:11.964 --> 36:13.882
[French Accent]
And I'll never forget,

36:13.882 --> 36:16.301
He said, "I am not
an animal,

36:16.301 --> 36:17.719
I am a human being,"

36:20.180 --> 36:22.891
Oh, darling, please
try one of my oysters,

36:23.099 --> 36:24.517
Oh,

36:24.517 --> 36:26.310
[Slurp]

36:26.436 --> 36:27.687
Formidable.

36:27.853 --> 36:28.729
Mmm,,, mmm!

36:28.854 --> 36:30.106
Oh, Pascal,

36:30.231 --> 36:32.066
for the gods,
For the gods!

36:32.191 --> 36:34.068
You should try it,
Hector,

36:34.068 --> 36:35.444
Not on
your life,

36:35.569 --> 36:36.862
[Doorbell
Rings]

36:36.987 --> 36:37.779
Oh,

36:37.863 --> 36:38.780
EXcuse me,

36:42.742 --> 36:45.620
Patsy! Well, Jimmie Lee
told me you were in Mexico

36:45.620 --> 36:46.954
and couldn't make it!

36:47.163 --> 36:48.789
I was just sick
about that!

36:48.956 --> 36:51.292
Well, I was!
I cut my trip short,

36:51.333 --> 36:54.670
Do you think I'd miss
Melly's going-away party?

36:54.753 --> 36:56.088
Can I help?

36:56.129 --> 36:58.965
We'll just have to
squeeze in another plate somehow,

36:59.049 --> 37:00.717
[Bump]
I hate it here!

37:02.802 --> 37:05.680
I told you this was
a formal dinner party,

37:05.680 --> 37:07.515
I want it to be
perfect for Melanie,

37:07.598 --> 37:09.517
I would have paid
for a baby-sitter,

37:09.517 --> 37:12.394
I know, But Jane says
we shouldn't exclude Bump,

37:12.394 --> 37:13.854
or he might be, um,,,

37:13.854 --> 37:15.063
scarred,

37:15.063 --> 37:16.565
Scarred
by the separation,

37:16.648 --> 37:19.401
Don't worry, Mrs, Greenway,
Bump should be here,

37:19.609 --> 37:20.860
He's your
great-grandchild,

37:20.944 --> 37:23.196
Besides, he's perfectly
behaved, I promise,

37:23.238 --> 37:25.615
I wanna go home!

37:25.656 --> 37:27.950
So you never
discipline?

37:28.034 --> 37:28.618
Huh,

37:31.120 --> 37:32.538
Attention, please,

37:32.579 --> 37:33.914
[Bump Laughing]

37:36.708 --> 37:37.959
Bump: When are
we gonna be through?

37:38.085 --> 37:39.502
I require silence,

37:39.544 --> 37:41.087
Butthole!

37:45.383 --> 37:47.718
Just a few words,
really,

37:47.802 --> 37:49.261
First of all,,,

37:49.261 --> 37:50.096
[Bump Laughing]

37:50.221 --> 37:51.805
Thank you all for coming,

37:53.390 --> 37:54.516
Arthur,

37:54.600 --> 37:57.394
thank you for
the absolutely gorgeous roses

37:57.436 --> 38:00.188
that you have
provided for our table,

38:00.230 --> 38:03.566
Pascal, the oysters
were delicious,

38:05.860 --> 38:08.738
Hector, your knowledge
of fine wines is unparalleled,

38:08.738 --> 38:09.947
Hector, your knowledge
of fine wines is unparalleled,

38:09.947 --> 38:11.991
[Bump Laughs]

38:12.116 --> 38:13.283
Jerry,

38:17.704 --> 38:18.914
[Clears Throat]

38:18.955 --> 38:23.585
You have become my bridge
over shark infested waters,

38:25.336 --> 38:26.295
J...

38:30.257 --> 38:33.260
Teddy, my darling
sweet Teddy,

38:33.260 --> 38:35.220
and your,,,

38:35.220 --> 38:36.263
Jane,

38:36.263 --> 38:38.390
To my Rosie,

38:38.431 --> 38:41.184
my right hand,
my right arm,

38:41.267 --> 38:42.602
my Rosie,

38:43.895 --> 38:44.812
And Patsy,

38:44.854 --> 38:46.814
who is always there
no matter what,

38:46.814 --> 38:48.607
[Bump Laughs]

38:48.691 --> 38:49.734
Bruce?

38:49.817 --> 38:51.485
Yeah?

38:51.569 --> 38:53.570
You are taking
our Melanie away,

38:54.947 --> 38:55.948
Words fail me,

38:56.031 --> 38:59.951
And to my darling
sweet precious Melanie,

39:00.035 --> 39:01.494
May your journey
be joyous,

39:01.536 --> 39:04.831
May your every
dream come true,

39:04.914 --> 39:06.457
And may you hurry back
to those who really love you,

39:06.457 --> 39:07.416
Aaahhh!

39:07.416 --> 39:08.459
Ah!

39:10.503 --> 39:13.047
Dessert is served
in the living room,

39:29.603 --> 39:30.938
She's playing
the piano, Pats,

39:31.146 --> 39:34.650
I can't remember
the last time she played,

39:34.733 --> 39:36.652
Something
is going on,

39:38.111 --> 39:40.530
Well, that Jerry
could make me play the piano,

39:40.655 --> 39:43.283
and I have never
even touched one,

39:43.366 --> 39:44.534
Know what I'm saying?

39:45.910 --> 39:47.495
Oh, here,

39:49.038 --> 39:49.830
Oh, Patsy,

39:49.914 --> 39:51.999
This is for you,

39:52.041 --> 39:53.208
With my love,

39:53.250 --> 39:54.418
Thank you,

39:55.836 --> 39:57.671
Oh, that's sweet,

39:57.754 --> 39:59.089
Oh, my,,,

39:59.214 --> 40:00.799
Patsy!

40:00.840 --> 40:02.217
This is too much,

40:02.300 --> 40:03.384
Just in case,

40:03.593 --> 40:04.969
How much is here?

40:05.011 --> 40:06.387
I can't believe,,,

40:06.471 --> 40:07.763
Just put it
away now.

40:07.805 --> 40:09.140
And don't tell Aurora,

40:09.265 --> 40:10.599
or she'd freak,
You know?

40:10.683 --> 40:12.142
I don't want to
ruin her evening,

40:12.142 --> 40:13.268
just her life,

40:14.561 --> 40:15.771
I'm kidding,

40:17.939 --> 40:19.232
Now,

40:19.232 --> 40:21.109
I can never hate anyone
who loves you kids

40:21.234 --> 40:22.485
as much as I do,

40:24.070 --> 40:27.657
Even if hers is
the kamikaze kind,

40:29.283 --> 40:30.242
Patsy,

40:30.367 --> 40:32.870
thank you
for everything,

40:32.870 --> 40:35.038
You're welcome,
sweetie,

40:59.603 --> 41:00.520
Hey,

41:00.562 --> 41:01.479
God,

41:01.479 --> 41:03.064
Did you see
what she gave me

41:03.064 --> 41:04.315
as a going
away present?

41:04.399 --> 41:05.316
What?

41:05.358 --> 41:07.109
A return ticket,

41:07.235 --> 41:08.653
That's...
That's too much,

41:08.694 --> 41:09.487
I know,

41:09.653 --> 41:11.989
Look at all this stuff,

41:12.031 --> 41:14.783
I feel like
I'm inside Aurora's head,

41:14.867 --> 41:16.785
She's such
a pack rat,

41:16.868 --> 41:17.661
Yeah,

41:17.786 --> 41:20.580
It's cleaner than
your room ever was.

41:20.580 --> 41:22.040
Oh no, it isn't,

41:26.002 --> 41:27.503
Look at this,

41:27.545 --> 41:28.546
Nice,

41:28.546 --> 41:30.214
Did you or Tommy
make this?

41:30.297 --> 41:32.466
I think that was me,

41:32.549 --> 41:34.051
Oh, look at Tommy,

41:34.134 --> 41:35.260
Oh, yeah,

41:39.139 --> 41:40.307
Wow,

41:40.348 --> 41:42.684
I was so blond,

41:42.767 --> 41:45.561
Once upon a time,
we were a family,

41:45.645 --> 41:46.896
Can you believe it?

41:46.979 --> 41:48.981
What was it like?

41:49.065 --> 41:50.357
Was it great?

41:53.444 --> 41:54.862
It had its moments,

41:56.655 --> 41:57.614
I um,,,

41:57.781 --> 41:59.699
I remember laughs,

41:59.783 --> 42:01.868
And uh... and hugs,
Lots of hugs,

42:01.951 --> 42:04.203
Mom was big on hugs,

42:04.203 --> 42:06.205
I guess she wanted
to hold onto us

42:06.330 --> 42:07.540
as long as she could,

42:09.166 --> 42:11.961
I wish I could
remember, Teddy,

42:11.961 --> 42:13.962
You're lucky,

42:19.467 --> 42:20.885
Stand up for a second,

42:20.969 --> 42:21.845
Why?

42:21.886 --> 42:22.971
- On your feet,
- Why should I?

42:23.054 --> 42:23.888
Stand up,

42:24.013 --> 42:24.889
For what?

42:24.931 --> 42:26.265
I'm not asking again,
On your feet,

42:29.769 --> 42:30.644
Mm-hmm,

42:35.482 --> 42:36.400
Now laugh,

42:40.070 --> 42:41.988
See?
There you go,

42:42.030 --> 42:43.740
Just like old times,

42:46.200 --> 42:48.369
Hey, be careful, O, K,?

42:49.787 --> 42:51.080
I will!

42:52.164 --> 42:53.082
You better,

42:53.165 --> 42:54.541
Pascal, it was

42:54.583 --> 42:57.002
so delightful
to have you, really,

42:57.085 --> 42:59.296
Aurora, darling, thank you
for a wonderful evening,

43:00.505 --> 43:02.298
Pascal, it's been great,

43:06.052 --> 43:06.886
Bonsoir.

43:12.349 --> 43:13.434
Good night, Hector,

43:24.819 --> 43:26.737
Yeah? Why is that?

43:26.821 --> 43:29.365
Well, there's a lot
of beefy people,,,

43:55.847 --> 43:57.015
So nice
to have met you,

43:57.099 --> 43:58.141
Yeah, Maybe
I'll see you again,

43:58.183 --> 43:59.351
See you again,

44:00.435 --> 44:01.269
Tramp!

44:04.689 --> 44:06.732
I don't like
the looks of this,

44:06.732 --> 44:08.734
You sure that's gonna
pass muster?

44:08.859 --> 44:09.944
Yeah, I've done it
a million times,

44:10.069 --> 44:11.904
You take care
of my baby,

44:11.946 --> 44:13.364
She's my baby now,

44:13.405 --> 44:14.281
Aw, honey,

44:15.407 --> 44:16.742
Come on, Hector,

44:22.455 --> 44:24.749
I'm not leaving
until you say something,

44:29.420 --> 44:30.629
Shit,

44:34.466 --> 44:35.300
Good morning!

44:36.385 --> 44:37.594
Be nice,

44:39.679 --> 44:41.598
I just had
to say good-bye!

44:41.681 --> 44:43.433
Come on,
give me a hug!

44:43.558 --> 44:44.600
Bye, Patsy,

44:44.767 --> 44:46.352
All right, Here now,
this is for you, handsome,

44:46.394 --> 44:48.354
Thank you,

44:48.646 --> 44:49.188
All right, Patsy,
enough, There's traffic,

44:49.188 --> 44:50.731
and they're
going to be late,

44:50.731 --> 44:51.857
Give me a kiss,

44:54.359 --> 44:55.569
Now, you be a good girl,

44:55.694 --> 44:57.362
You have a wonderful trip
and call constantly,

44:57.446 --> 44:58.280
I will!

44:58.405 --> 45:00.240
Call as soon
as you can.

45:00.282 --> 45:01.199
Melanie: Bye,

45:01.282 --> 45:02.158
Bye,

45:02.242 --> 45:03.117
[Car Clanking]

45:10.291 --> 45:12.668
You know, you've been good
about this, Aurora,

45:14.670 --> 45:16.004
Everyone needs to
experience happiness,

45:16.046 --> 45:17.756
even if
it doesn't last,

45:17.798 --> 45:19.216
[Cars Bump Loudly]

45:20.383 --> 45:25.179
Oh, she reminds me
so much of Emma it hurts,

45:41.111 --> 45:41.945
[Doorbell Rings]

45:42.070 --> 45:43.905
Come in,
It's open,

45:46.741 --> 45:47.658
Hi,

45:47.700 --> 45:48.659
Hello, Jerry,

45:53.163 --> 45:54.081
Can I help you?

45:55.457 --> 45:57.793
Well, I couldn't help
but be a little bit curious

45:57.834 --> 45:59.711
as to why you didn't
come in today,

45:59.794 --> 46:02.755
I... I guess
it slipped my mind,

46:02.797 --> 46:03.965
Uh-huh,

46:04.007 --> 46:06.384
Well, now that I've let Melanie
live her own life

46:06.551 --> 46:08.010
and she's out of
mine for good,

46:08.010 --> 46:10.137
I presume
that I am cured,

46:10.262 --> 46:11.180
Oh, boy,

46:11.180 --> 46:12.139
What happened?

46:12.139 --> 46:13.307
Nothing,

46:13.307 --> 46:15.559
The party
was a triumph,

46:15.559 --> 46:18.520
You know it was like
a successful lab experiment,

46:18.562 --> 46:21.106
I put all the rats
together in one room

46:21.106 --> 46:22.565
to see if they'd
eat each other,

46:22.649 --> 46:24.651
Wha,,,

46:24.692 --> 46:26.569
O, K,, Aurora,

46:26.652 --> 46:29.447
you're talking this out,

46:29.488 --> 46:31.365
I'm taking you to dinner,

46:31.448 --> 46:33.033
You name it,

46:33.117 --> 46:34.952
Money's no object,

46:36.620 --> 46:38.038
Hi, trudy,

46:38.205 --> 46:39.080
Hi!

46:39.206 --> 46:40.040
Hi, Aurora,

46:40.040 --> 46:41.499
She's the best
cook here,

46:41.583 --> 46:42.459
Hi, boys,

46:42.542 --> 46:43.918
Hey, Miss G,

46:45.336 --> 46:46.587
Here we are,

46:47.338 --> 46:48.214
Hello, darling,

46:48.214 --> 46:49.548
Hi, honey,

46:49.632 --> 46:51.133
Thank you,

46:51.133 --> 46:52.760
You come here?

46:52.843 --> 46:54.344
Yes, I eat here
every Sunday

46:54.470 --> 46:55.929
on my way
to visit Tommy,

46:55.929 --> 46:58.348
I get great strength
from their pecan pie,

46:58.431 --> 47:00.100
You find this
uncomfortable?

47:00.183 --> 47:02.060
No, it's just,,,

47:02.102 --> 47:04.896
I just wouldn't expect you
to come to a place like this,

47:04.979 --> 47:06.355
Jerry,
I'm very liberal,

47:06.439 --> 47:08.899
and I embrace
all kinds of humanity,

47:08.983 --> 47:10.484
just like you do,

47:12.069 --> 47:13.570
Besides, I thought
this was the safest place

47:13.654 --> 47:14.863
to bring you
on a date,

47:16.031 --> 47:17.407
This is a date?

47:18.742 --> 47:19.618
Aurora,

47:19.701 --> 47:21.995
I'm going to
take you to dinner,

47:23.204 --> 47:24.580
Now,
here in America,

47:24.664 --> 47:25.998
we call that
a date,

47:26.082 --> 47:28.417
Maybe it's not
a date in the sense

47:28.501 --> 47:29.960
that we're on our way
to sleeping together,

47:29.960 --> 47:32.379
Which would really be
a preposterous idea,

47:32.504 --> 47:34.131
Dolly, could I have, please,

47:34.339 --> 47:35.716
the pig platter
with french fries, cole slaw,

47:35.716 --> 47:37.092
a double order
of beans,

47:37.217 --> 47:38.093
uh... iced tea

47:38.135 --> 47:39.302
and some
sweet n' low?

47:39.344 --> 47:42.514
And for you,
young man?

47:42.555 --> 47:44.015
The same,

47:45.516 --> 47:47.435
Why is that such
a preposterous idea?

47:47.518 --> 47:48.561
Let's discuss that,

47:48.644 --> 47:49.520
Discuss what?

47:51.230 --> 47:52.231
Oh,

47:52.231 --> 47:53.607
Do you want
to sleep with me?

47:58.195 --> 47:59.654
Would that be so bad?

48:01.990 --> 48:03.741
Oh, Jerry,

48:03.783 --> 48:05.368
You know,
if I slept with you,

48:05.410 --> 48:06.744
I would be lost,

48:06.869 --> 48:09.413
I'd be lost on so many,
many levels,

48:11.248 --> 48:14.168
Really, it would just be
another empty conquest,

48:15.919 --> 48:18.755
Then I would be like all
those other predatory females

48:18.839 --> 48:22.217
prowling the streets
of Houston,

48:24.302 --> 48:26.304
This is about Patsy,
isn't it?

48:27.847 --> 48:28.889
Tell me,

48:31.684 --> 48:33.852
Patsy is not my type,

48:37.147 --> 48:38.648
Thanks, doll,

48:41.192 --> 48:42.610
What is your type?

48:44.404 --> 48:45.696
Same as
every other guy,

48:47.031 --> 48:47.990
Really big tits,

48:49.617 --> 48:51.160
Dumb as a post,

48:51.202 --> 48:52.411
Oh, the younger
the better,

48:54.329 --> 48:55.330
Ha ha,

49:14.014 --> 49:15.641
[Television On]

49:27.735 --> 49:29.362
Hector?

49:29.362 --> 49:31.155
Is there something wrong
with your television?

49:31.238 --> 49:32.614
My cable's out,

49:32.698 --> 49:34.616
It's
our favorite movie,

49:35.909 --> 49:36.743
Sit down,

49:47.461 --> 49:48.504
[Men Whistling]

49:53.300 --> 49:54.468
What?

49:56.219 --> 49:57.304
Close your eyes,

49:58.638 --> 49:59.598
Why?

49:59.681 --> 50:00.807
Just close them,

50:06.771 --> 50:08.397
I want you to think
about the moment

50:08.481 --> 50:09.565
you first laid
eyes on me.

50:09.607 --> 50:12.401
At the river oaks
country club,

50:12.484 --> 50:14.820
In my dress blues,

50:14.903 --> 50:15.737
Mm-hmm,

50:17.739 --> 50:20.533
No one could fill out a uniform
the way you could,

50:23.036 --> 50:24.412
Yeah,

50:24.495 --> 50:27.248
You were so strong,
Hector,

50:27.331 --> 50:29.917
And I needed
your strength so much,

50:31.460 --> 50:32.836
So did the children,

50:32.836 --> 50:34.379
Mmm,

50:34.463 --> 50:36.840
You were so wonderful,

50:36.965 --> 50:38.300
I'm still wonderful,

50:41.219 --> 50:43.763
Oh, yes,
you are still wonderful,

50:50.603 --> 50:51.520
Huh?

50:51.562 --> 50:52.688
I got cold,

50:59.569 --> 51:00.695
[Snoring]

51:30.347 --> 51:31.182
Oh,

51:57.998 --> 51:58.832
[Banging]

52:17.891 --> 52:19.017
Aaahhh!

52:19.100 --> 52:19.935
Oh!

52:20.060 --> 52:21.102
How rude!

52:21.144 --> 52:23.229
Christ, Aurora!
What the hell are you doing?

52:23.229 --> 52:24.439
It's 2:00
in the morning,

52:24.480 --> 52:25.690
Well, I am upset

52:25.815 --> 52:27.149
and I want
to feel better,

52:27.233 --> 52:28.609
And it's your business,

52:28.651 --> 52:30.486
You did say anytime
of the day or night,

52:30.653 --> 52:32.446
I want to talk,

52:32.613 --> 52:35.282
You didn't come here
just to talk,

52:35.407 --> 52:37.200
Yes, I did,

52:37.284 --> 52:39.160
Well, no, I didn't,

52:39.202 --> 52:40.120
Oh!

52:42.580 --> 52:44.582
Is it safe to leave
my car on the street?

52:44.749 --> 52:46.083
Oh!

53:00.638 --> 53:01.514
Ah!

53:25.203 --> 53:26.621
[Radio Goes On]

53:26.621 --> 53:28.748
Morning, Houston.
Time to rise and shine!

53:36.296 --> 53:39.382
I didn't know
what time it was

53:39.507 --> 53:41.885
Then I met you

53:41.968 --> 53:45.430
Oh, what a lovely
time it was

53:45.555 --> 53:48.349
How sublime it was, too

53:48.432 --> 53:52.061
I didn't know
what day it was

53:52.061 --> 53:53.020
You helped...

53:53.020 --> 53:53.937
[Humming]

53:56.189 --> 53:57.065
Jerry,

53:58.817 --> 53:59.985
Oh, good morning,

53:59.985 --> 54:01.069
Good morning,

54:03.404 --> 54:05.198
Aurora, look, I'm sorry
about last night,

54:05.281 --> 54:06.782
I don't know
what came over me

54:06.908 --> 54:08.117
or what
possessed me,

54:08.159 --> 54:09.035
I'm really,
really,,,

54:09.160 --> 54:10.744
sorry.

54:10.744 --> 54:12.538
I'm going
to leave now

54:12.663 --> 54:15.040
or I'll be embarrassed
by your flattery,

54:15.165 --> 54:16.083
No, wait!

54:16.166 --> 54:17.459
No! No,
no wait, wait!

54:37.269 --> 54:39.020
Well, I'm not hungry,

54:42.815 --> 54:44.150
I'm not surprised,

54:56.036 --> 54:56.995
Hi, baby,

54:57.120 --> 54:58.914
I found some
barbecue today

54:58.914 --> 55:02.041
and it's almost
as good as Good Company,

55:02.083 --> 55:03.501
Are you hungry?

55:03.501 --> 55:04.836
No,

55:05.837 --> 55:08.339
Oh, you got your pictures,
Let me see 'em,

55:08.464 --> 55:09.715
Let me see 'em,

55:09.799 --> 55:10.633
They suck,

55:10.758 --> 55:12.092
No, they're
gonna be great,

55:12.217 --> 55:13.719
I'm telling you
they suck bad!

55:15.012 --> 55:16.888
Bruce, I want
to see them,

55:19.182 --> 55:20.183
Bruce?

55:20.266 --> 55:23.394
How could any picture
of yours ever be bad?

55:27.565 --> 55:29.191
It's not bad,

55:29.316 --> 55:30.568
It's... It's,,,

55:30.734 --> 55:31.694
Melanie: Good,

55:40.410 --> 55:42.287
Look,
all you have to do

55:42.287 --> 55:43.705
is just get better
pictures made,

55:43.746 --> 55:44.664
That's all,

55:44.706 --> 55:45.998
With what?

55:46.040 --> 55:48.959
Our disposable income
has been disposed of,

55:49.043 --> 55:50.461
You can't call Aurora,

55:57.801 --> 56:00.970
I'm getting a little
perturbed with Melly, actually,

56:01.012 --> 56:02.931
You think she would
have picked up a phone

56:02.931 --> 56:04.390
and said I'm in L, A,

56:04.390 --> 56:06.350
I've arrived,
I'm alive,

56:06.434 --> 56:08.144
It's been
much too long,

56:08.185 --> 56:10.146
Yeah well, you know,

56:10.187 --> 56:12.940
things have been
kind of crazy for her,

56:15.484 --> 56:16.735
Have you talked to her?

56:16.860 --> 56:17.944
Yeah,

56:18.069 --> 56:20.697
She had some kind of
unexpected expense,

56:20.739 --> 56:22.115
so I made her
a little loan,

56:23.491 --> 56:25.868
Boy, that kid's
got spunk,

56:27.453 --> 56:30.080
I cannot find
a thing, anymore,

56:31.248 --> 56:34.585
Shopping is just
so frustrating these days,

56:34.668 --> 56:38.880
Oh, Patsy, you always find
such wonderful things,

56:39.005 --> 56:40.799
I mean, look at you,

56:40.799 --> 56:43.218
So perfectly
put together,

56:43.384 --> 56:45.011
I love that belt,

56:45.011 --> 56:48.139
It is hard to find
the right yellow,

56:54.394 --> 56:56.313
You know, I bet that Melly's
tried to reach you,

56:56.313 --> 57:00.567
But Rosie says you're
never home anymore,

57:00.650 --> 57:02.235
She says you're
always in therapy,

57:03.611 --> 57:05.279
You must be about
the most well-adjusted

57:05.363 --> 57:06.697
woman in Houston by now,

57:06.781 --> 57:08.282
Well, it's doing
wonders for me,

57:08.407 --> 57:09.658
[Giggles]

57:09.742 --> 57:12.536
Tell me about Jerry,

57:12.661 --> 57:14.037
He's very
attractive,

57:14.037 --> 57:15.581
Mm-hmm, I like him,

57:17.332 --> 57:19.251
Is that line between
doctor and patient

57:19.251 --> 57:21.920
getting
a little blurred?

57:22.045 --> 57:24.047
What do you think?

57:24.130 --> 57:25.381
Hmm,

57:27.091 --> 57:28.551
Be honest,

57:28.592 --> 57:31.136
Doesn't the fact that
I'm older disgust you?

57:31.136 --> 57:32.429
You don't
seem older,

57:32.554 --> 57:33.931
But I am older,
Jerry,

57:33.931 --> 57:36.516
And I have all the insecurities
that go along with it,

57:36.516 --> 57:38.852
So if you're not
gonna help me with them,

57:38.894 --> 57:39.936
don't lie,

57:43.648 --> 57:45.942
You are too much,

57:46.067 --> 57:48.736
I have always felt that
I'd better just keep trying,

57:48.861 --> 57:52.448
Especially when the world around me
seems to have stopped,

57:52.614 --> 57:54.199
When you stop trying,

57:54.241 --> 57:55.951
you fade away,

57:55.993 --> 57:57.619
And I am not
going to fade away

57:57.619 --> 57:59.454
until I absolutely
have to,

57:59.579 --> 58:02.332
Something somewhere,,,

58:02.415 --> 58:05.001
is going to say
Aurora was here,

58:11.340 --> 58:12.883
Well, what do you know?

58:12.966 --> 58:15.302
Herself has
come home for a change,

58:15.344 --> 58:17.304
Don't be too hard on her,

58:17.304 --> 58:20.015
She's just
enjoying her life,

58:21.099 --> 58:22.517
It wouldn't hurt you
to kick up your heels

58:22.642 --> 58:25.061
like that
every now and then,

58:26.437 --> 58:27.980
Arthur,

58:29.231 --> 58:30.649
Oh, hello, Hector,

58:30.691 --> 58:33.068
We care about you,

58:33.068 --> 58:35.070
We feel you're making
a big mistake,

58:35.988 --> 58:36.988
Well,

58:38.406 --> 58:40.200
Oh, Hector, I have come
to the conclusion

58:40.283 --> 58:43.119
there's no such thing
as a mistake,

58:43.203 --> 58:45.163
I think we all
create what we need,

58:53.337 --> 58:54.546
[Piano Music On]

59:00.093 --> 59:01.636
[Music Stops]

59:01.719 --> 59:04.514
Rosie,
what in the world?

59:04.597 --> 59:06.265
I'm sick of this,

59:06.265 --> 59:08.059
Sick of what?

59:08.059 --> 59:10.519
You and Hector
are so cranky,

59:10.644 --> 59:12.271
You never spend
time with us anymore,

59:14.064 --> 59:14.982
I live here,

59:14.982 --> 59:15.983
Barely,

59:17.150 --> 59:18.818
You're always off
with that damn Jerry

59:18.902 --> 59:20.487
or holed up in here,

59:20.612 --> 59:21.946
Instead of spending
so much time

59:21.946 --> 59:23.531
on those stupid
scrap books,

59:23.531 --> 59:26.409
you should spend time
on the people in 'em,

59:42.382 --> 59:44.258
Hector,

59:44.258 --> 59:47.053
What do you say
we have some fun?

59:47.094 --> 59:48.012
Huh?

59:48.137 --> 59:50.055
Get dressed,
I'm taking us to dinner,

59:55.352 --> 59:57.354
Hector, move in
just a speck,

59:57.396 --> 59:59.731
Rosie, take your hand down
from your face, please,

01:00:02.192 --> 01:00:03.610
You're so silly,

01:00:03.735 --> 01:00:06.571
Dolly, we're ready for
the big finish now,

01:00:06.571 --> 01:00:07.905
O, K,, honey,
what'll it be?

01:00:07.947 --> 01:00:08.864
This is the General's
big night out,

01:00:08.948 --> 01:00:10.282
He'll go first,

01:00:21.259 --> 01:00:22.844
I'll have
the pecan pie,

01:00:23.969 --> 01:00:24.845
Dolly: Mm-hmm,

01:00:23.387 --> 01:00:24.347
Rosie, what will
you have?

01:00:24.472 --> 01:00:25.681
Um,,,

01:00:25.681 --> 01:00:27.641
banana split,

01:00:27.683 --> 01:00:29.101
Oh, that's it, Rosie,
live a little,

01:00:29.143 --> 01:00:30.769
How about you,
Dr, Cotton?

01:00:30.853 --> 01:00:33.397
I'll have
the super sundae,

01:00:33.522 --> 01:00:34.439
[Dolly And Rosie]
Whoo!

01:00:34.439 --> 01:00:35.315
Fudge,

01:00:35.398 --> 01:00:36.900
Yes!

01:00:38.234 --> 01:00:41.571
And Hector I'm sure
will have the mince pie,

01:00:41.654 --> 01:00:43.156
Dolly: You want that
a la mode, darling?

01:00:44.991 --> 01:00:46.242
Hector, do you want
it a la mode?

01:00:51.163 --> 01:00:53.165
Hector?

01:00:53.165 --> 01:00:54.207
Hector?

01:01:03.706 --> 01:01:05.291
[Bagpipes Playing]

01:01:25.603 --> 01:01:28.439
There is something
very wrong with you,

01:01:43.245 --> 01:01:44.329
Going back
to old Jerry?

01:01:46.331 --> 01:01:48.291
I'm surprised
you've waited this long,

01:01:48.333 --> 01:01:51.544
The General's been in the ground
almost 5 hours,

01:01:51.669 --> 01:01:54.463
I'm looking for
the love of my life, Rosie,

01:01:54.505 --> 01:01:58.258
And it's important that I
investigate every possibility,

01:02:11.687 --> 01:02:12.647
Rosie?

01:02:19.069 --> 01:02:20.946
Is everything
all right, Rosie?

01:02:23.865 --> 01:02:25.200
No,

01:02:25.283 --> 01:02:27.368
Come on, talk to me,

01:02:29.287 --> 01:02:30.288
Come on,

01:02:31.455 --> 01:02:32.707
Everything's
gonna be all right,

01:02:34.792 --> 01:02:36.001
Everything's all right,

01:02:38.962 --> 01:02:43.883
Oh, that chapter
on Hector Scott is closed,

01:02:45.343 --> 01:02:47.637
It's a very
important chapter, too,

01:02:49.555 --> 01:02:50.932
Hmm,

01:02:51.015 --> 01:02:52.433
You know keeping
this grown-up

01:02:52.558 --> 01:02:54.768
was the best thing
I've ever done?

01:02:54.935 --> 01:02:56.061
What do you think?

01:02:56.145 --> 01:02:58.981
Will I rate
a whole page?

01:03:01.900 --> 01:03:02.734
We'll see,

01:03:05.779 --> 01:03:06.696
Aurora?

01:03:06.738 --> 01:03:07.530
Hmm?

01:03:10.616 --> 01:03:12.451
I love you,

01:03:14.370 --> 01:03:15.663
Um,,,

01:03:15.704 --> 01:03:16.580
what?

01:03:18.457 --> 01:03:19.833
I have to
think about that,

01:03:19.958 --> 01:03:21.209
All is said
was I love you,

01:03:21.418 --> 01:03:23.170
Yes, and it's
very flattering,

01:03:24.879 --> 01:03:26.506
Don't you believe
that I love you?

01:03:26.589 --> 01:03:28.883
Oh yes, I can see
where you would,

01:03:31.761 --> 01:03:33.179
I just did not
receive the information

01:03:33.179 --> 01:03:34.638
the way I thought
I would,

01:03:36.557 --> 01:03:37.599
This is my problem,
Jerry,

01:03:41.853 --> 01:03:42.813
Aurora?

01:03:46.232 --> 01:03:49.068
You don't have to go back
to Los Angeles, Stay,

01:03:49.068 --> 01:03:50.862
I've been here
a week as it is,

01:03:50.945 --> 01:03:52.697
Rosie: Well, just
through the weekend,

01:03:52.780 --> 01:03:54.782
I can't, I have
a boyfriend and a job,

01:03:54.865 --> 01:03:56.700
As a waitress,

01:03:56.784 --> 01:03:59.119
Things are really
starting to click for Bruce,

01:03:59.203 --> 01:04:00.704
And I knew they would,

01:04:00.787 --> 01:04:03.915
His acting teacher says
he's like an open wound,

01:04:03.999 --> 01:04:05.792
He's up for
a beer commercial,

01:04:06.960 --> 01:04:08.294
I'm really happy,

01:04:08.419 --> 01:04:10.546
Melanie,
I hate this,

01:04:10.588 --> 01:04:12.214
I hate that you're
going away again,

01:04:12.340 --> 01:04:13.966
I never know
where you are,

01:04:13.966 --> 01:04:15.342
I worry
all the time,

01:04:15.509 --> 01:04:17.261
I have to go through Patsy
to get to you,

01:04:17.344 --> 01:04:18.428
I really hate that,

01:04:18.554 --> 01:04:19.680
O, K,

01:04:21.139 --> 01:04:22.766
I'll give you
my phone number,

01:04:24.059 --> 01:04:26.769
If you'll promise me
you'll never ever use it,

01:04:30.231 --> 01:04:32.066
I promise,

01:04:40.407 --> 01:04:41.408
Finally,

01:04:43.785 --> 01:04:44.786
You're so late!

01:04:44.911 --> 01:04:45.787
I know,

01:04:47.580 --> 01:04:48.915
Is everything O, K,?

01:04:48.998 --> 01:04:49.957
Mel?

01:04:49.957 --> 01:04:51.334
Yeah?

01:04:51.459 --> 01:04:52.960
There's something
I gotta tell you,

01:04:53.044 --> 01:04:54.503
Yeah?

01:04:56.547 --> 01:04:57.840
I got the commercial,

01:04:57.965 --> 01:04:59.883
Ah!
You did?!

01:05:00.967 --> 01:05:02.135
That is so good,
honey,

01:05:02.302 --> 01:05:03.094
Yeah,

01:05:05.847 --> 01:05:07.599
So are you the beer drinker
in the ski parka

01:05:07.682 --> 01:05:09.517
or the one
in the Speedo?

01:05:09.517 --> 01:05:10.434
Speedo,

01:05:11.644 --> 01:05:13.104
They're no fools,

01:05:14.396 --> 01:05:16.815
Oh, it's so good
to be home,

01:05:24.281 --> 01:05:25.740
Mel?

01:05:25.782 --> 01:05:27.408
The whole point
of us coming to L, A,

01:05:27.408 --> 01:05:29.118
was to make a new start,

01:05:29.118 --> 01:05:30.620
I've been meaning
to talk to you

01:05:30.703 --> 01:05:32.580
about this for
a few weeks now,

01:05:32.580 --> 01:05:34.707
But... But then,
Hector died

01:05:34.748 --> 01:05:37.334
and you were
so bummed out, so,,,

01:05:44.215 --> 01:05:46.301
Does it have a name?

01:05:46.342 --> 01:05:47.510
Yeah,

01:05:49.053 --> 01:05:50.638
She um,,,

01:05:50.638 --> 01:05:52.640
She's helped me
a lot with my career,

01:05:54.517 --> 01:05:58.061
Bruce,
do you have any idea

01:05:58.061 --> 01:06:00.230
what this
does to me?

01:06:00.355 --> 01:06:02.399
Yeah, I think I do,

01:06:02.482 --> 01:06:04.609
I think I do, but,,,

01:06:04.609 --> 01:06:06.361
it's not aimed
at you, Mel,

01:06:06.361 --> 01:06:08.613
It may not be
aimed at me,

01:06:08.613 --> 01:06:10.781
but it hits me,
and it hurts,

01:06:10.781 --> 01:06:12.408
Shit!

01:06:12.491 --> 01:06:14.368
This means Granny
was right,

01:06:14.410 --> 01:06:16.120
I could just
kill you!

01:06:16.120 --> 01:06:17.454
Just get out!

01:06:17.538 --> 01:06:18.413
O, K,

01:06:20.707 --> 01:06:22.667
Can I ask you
something?

01:06:22.667 --> 01:06:24.085
What?!

01:06:24.085 --> 01:06:27.088
I didn't get a chance
to forward my Varieties,

01:06:27.088 --> 01:06:30.383
and I need them for audition
notices, Can you hold onto them?

01:06:30.466 --> 01:06:31.592
Out!

01:06:31.634 --> 01:06:33.219
Thanks,

01:06:33.260 --> 01:06:35.638
Ooh!

01:06:55.155 --> 01:06:56.156
Hi,

01:06:56.156 --> 01:06:57.491
Remember me?

01:06:57.533 --> 01:06:59.159
I'm Patsy,

01:07:00.619 --> 01:07:03.705
I don't think I've met
anybody quite like you,

01:07:03.788 --> 01:07:05.248
Patsy Carpenter,

01:07:06.833 --> 01:07:08.042
Why?

01:07:09.085 --> 01:07:11.837
A bored, rich
Houston divorcee?

01:07:13.381 --> 01:07:15.257
Oh, well, Ha ha,

01:07:15.299 --> 01:07:17.134
We're not exactly
a rare breed,

01:07:17.259 --> 01:07:20.012
I tend to stay away
from upper class women,

01:07:20.095 --> 01:07:22.180
They scare me,

01:07:24.182 --> 01:07:25.934
Make me feel
uncomfortable,

01:07:26.017 --> 01:07:27.393
I'm hardly upper class,

01:07:27.435 --> 01:07:30.146
You know, I'm just
a poor little old Texas gal,

01:07:30.354 --> 01:07:32.565
Struck oil
at the altar,

01:07:35.192 --> 01:07:37.736
Now,,, Aurora,,,

01:07:37.861 --> 01:07:39.696
she's upper class,

01:07:39.738 --> 01:07:41.615
Yeah, she is,

01:07:41.698 --> 01:07:44.492
Do you feel
uncomfortable with her?

01:07:44.659 --> 01:07:46.494
Well, I,,,

01:07:46.494 --> 01:07:49.247
I don't know what's going on
with Aurora right now,

01:07:49.330 --> 01:07:50.706
It's...

01:07:50.832 --> 01:07:52.958
Well, let's just say
it's complicated,

01:07:54.668 --> 01:07:55.753
I'll bet,

01:08:03.009 --> 01:08:04.135
Trouble?

01:08:05.887 --> 01:08:08.681
Well, I'm not really
at liberty to discuss her,

01:08:08.806 --> 01:08:10.600
She is a patient,

01:08:10.766 --> 01:08:12.685
Oh!

01:08:12.768 --> 01:08:16.145
The old
doctor/ patient thing,

01:08:16.188 --> 01:08:17.106
Yeah,

01:08:18.439 --> 01:08:21.693
But you're not really
a doctor, are you?

01:08:21.818 --> 01:08:24.738
That's right,
I'm not,

01:08:24.863 --> 01:08:27.657
But I do try to
follow the rules,

01:08:27.698 --> 01:08:29.533
Hear no evil,
Speak no evil,

01:08:29.658 --> 01:08:31.285
Do no evil?

01:08:35.413 --> 01:08:37.416
You're fascinating,

01:08:37.416 --> 01:08:38.667
No,

01:08:38.750 --> 01:08:40.669
You're fascinating,

01:08:41.837 --> 01:08:43.964
It's fascinating,,,

01:08:44.005 --> 01:08:47.300
that a man like you should be
sleeping with a woman

01:08:47.383 --> 01:08:49.551
who's old enough
to be,,,

01:08:49.594 --> 01:08:51.053
your mother,

01:08:53.055 --> 01:08:54.140
Bottoms up,

01:08:59.770 --> 01:09:02.564
So what does the rest
of the house look like?

01:09:02.647 --> 01:09:04.649
Why don't you
follow me?

01:09:07.068 --> 01:09:09.237
I haven't heard
from Melanie,

01:09:09.362 --> 01:09:12.238
and nothing compels me
to return to my therapist,

01:09:12.238 --> 01:09:15.201
I haven't seen much of Patsy,
either, thank God,

01:09:15.242 --> 01:09:17.118
Rosie is becoming
extremely difficult,

01:09:17.202 --> 01:09:20.037
I think it might be
because Hector's gone,

01:09:20.037 --> 01:09:21.581
That's no great loss,

01:09:21.665 --> 01:09:23.082
How can you say that?

01:09:23.207 --> 01:09:25.502
Hector loved you
and you loved him,

01:09:25.585 --> 01:09:29.630
If I heard "The military'd
straighten Tommy out" one more time,

01:09:29.756 --> 01:09:31.549
I'd have killed him
myself,

01:09:31.631 --> 01:09:33.551
Tell me how it works,
Tommy,

01:09:33.634 --> 01:09:37.095
When someone that you hate dies,
like the General,

01:09:37.136 --> 01:09:41.015
does the hatred that you feel
for that person dissipate,

01:09:41.099 --> 01:09:44.435
or do you transfer it
to someone else,,,

01:09:44.435 --> 01:09:45.310
like me?

01:09:45.395 --> 01:09:47.229
Would you explain this
to me, please?

01:09:47.313 --> 01:09:50.441
Because I do not understand
hatred as a sport,

01:09:50.441 --> 01:09:51.817
How does one win?

01:09:52.902 --> 01:09:54.862
Hey, eXcuse me,

01:09:54.987 --> 01:09:56.655
Sit down,

01:10:01.159 --> 01:10:03.036
Now do me a favor,

01:10:03.036 --> 01:10:04.996
I enjoy cooking
those brownies,

01:10:05.038 --> 01:10:06.331
That is my recipe,

01:10:06.414 --> 01:10:09.959
I have spent many years
perfecting it to get it right,

01:10:10.001 --> 01:10:12.962
I consider these brownies
to be the finest

01:10:13.045 --> 01:10:14.505
in the whole world,

01:10:14.505 --> 01:10:17.341
Please do not throw these brownies
away in front of me,

01:10:17.341 --> 01:10:20.302
You can take them and throw them
away after I'm gone

01:10:20.510 --> 01:10:21.762
if you want to,

01:10:21.845 --> 01:10:24.889
Just so you know,
I've put a file inside,

01:10:37.609 --> 01:10:38.569
Whatcha got?

01:10:38.652 --> 01:10:40.404
Merry Christmas,

01:11:40.500 --> 01:11:44.004
If I could fly
like birds on high

01:11:44.087 --> 01:11:45.880
Then straight to
her arms

01:11:46.089 --> 01:11:47.507
I'd go sailing

01:11:47.715 --> 01:11:48.716
Jerry,

